From: Vasilii Olekhov <olekhov@gmail.com>
Subject: [PATCH] uqmi: qmi.sh: set network roaming preference when roaming=1

vanilla qmi.sh accepts the UCI option roaming but never passes it to
uqmi. uqmi --start-network without --set-network-roaming defaults to
home-only, which allows the WDS bearer to be established (control plane)
but blocks user-plane traffic when the modem is in roaming.

Add roaming as a declared proto option and pass
--set-network-roaming any to --start-network when it is set.

Confirmed fix for Quectel EM060K-GL with a roaming eSIM profile
(EIOT Club / Proximus) on Cyta (MCC 280/01): user-plane traffic
was completely absent (TX only, RX zero) without this flag.

--- a/package/network/utils/uqmi/files/lib/netifd/proto/qmi.sh
+++ b/package/network/utils/uqmi/files/lib/netifd/proto/qmi.sh
@@ -27,6 +27,7 @@
 	proto_config_add_boolean sourcefilter
 	proto_config_add_boolean delegate
 	proto_config_add_boolean autoconnect
+	proto_config_add_boolean roaming
 	proto_config_add_int plmn
 	proto_config_add_int timeout
 	proto_config_add_int mtu
@@ -47,8 +48,8 @@
 	local apn auth delay device modes password pdptype pincode username v6apn
 	json_get_vars apn auth delay device modes password pdptype pincode username v6apn

-	local profile v6profile devpath dhcp dhcpv6 autoconnect plmn timeout
-	json_get_vars profile v6profile devpath dhcp dhcpv6 autoconnect plmn timeout
+	local profile v6profile devpath dhcp dhcpv6 autoconnect roaming plmn timeout
+	json_get_vars profile v6profile devpath dhcp dhcpv6 autoconnect roaming plmn timeout

 	[ "$timeout" = "" ] && timeout="10"

@@ -362,7 +363,8 @@
 			${auth:+--auth-type $auth} \
 			${username:+--username $username} \
 			${password:+--password $password} \
-			${autoconnect:+--autoconnect})
+			${autoconnect:+--autoconnect} \
+			${roaming:+--set-network-roaming any})

 		# pdh_4 is a numeric value on success
 		if ! [ "$pdh_4" -eq "$pdh_4" ] 2> /dev/null; then
